snippet: The timeline offered few new details and left many questions unanswered, such as why the two boats deviated from their course and strayed into Iran’s territorial waters.
abstract: Defense Dept timeline describing capture and return of 10 United States Navy sailors by Iran offers few specifics; officials say episode, which occurred amid delicate secret prisoner-swap negotiations between two countries and just as Iran completed its nuclear deal obligations, is still under review.
lead_paragraph: The timeline offered few new details and left many questions unanswered, such as why the two boats deviated from their course and strayed into Iran’s territorial waters.
